TB6612FNG Pin Overview

The module has two sides:
A. Power Pins
Pin	Name	Function
VM->	Motor Power->	5V–12V (motor supply)
VCC->	Logic Power->	5V (from Arduino)
GND->	Ground->	Common ground
STBY->	Standby->Enable pin
B. Motor A Control Pins
Pin->	Function
AIN1->	Direction control
AIN2->	Direction control
PWMA-> Speed control (PWM)
C. Motor B Control Pins
Pin->	Function
BIN1->	Direction control
BIN2-> Direction control
PWMB->	Speed control (PWM)
D. Output Pins (To Motors)
Pin->	Connects to
A01, A02->	Motor A
B01, B02-> Motor B
Connection with Arduino (Example)
✅ Motor A Connection
TB6612FNG	Arduino
VCC->	5V
GND	->GND
VM	->External battery (e.g., 7–12V)
STBY->	5V (or digital pin)
AIN1->	D7
AIN2	->D8
PWMA	->D5 (PWM pin)

✅ Motor B Connection (Optional)
TB6612FNG->	Arduino
BIN1->	D9
BIN2->	D10
PWMB->	D6 (PWM pin)
Motors
Motor A → A01 & A02
Motor B → B01 & B02
How Pins Work
Direction Control (AIN1, AIN2)
AIN1->	AIN2	->Motor Direction
HIGH	->LOW	->Forward
LOW	->HIGH	->Reverse
LOW	->LOW	->Stop
HIGH->	HIGH	->Brake
Speed Control (PWMA / PWMB)
Use PWM signal (0–255)
Controls motor speed
STBY (Standby Pin)
HIGH → Motor ON
LOW → Motor OFF
Must be HIGH to run motors
Important Notes

✔ Always use external power for motors (VM)
✔ Do NOT power motors from Arduino 5V
✔ Connect common GND between Arduino and driver
✔ Use PWM pins for speed control
